Class AbstractExprNodeVisitor<R>

java.lang.Object

      com.google.template.soy.exprtree.AbstractExprNodeVisitor<R>
Type Parameters:
R - The return type.
All Implemented Interfaces:

Direct Known Subclasses:
SubstituteGlobalsVisitor, TranslateToJavaExprVisitor, TranslateToJsExprVisitor
public abstract class AbstractExprNodeVisitor<R>
extends AbstractNodeVisitor<ExprNode,R>

Abstract base class for all ExprNode visitors. A visitor is basically a function implemented for some or all ExprNodes, where the implementation can be different for each specific node class.

Important: Do not use outside of Soy code (treat as superpackage-private).

  • Sets up calling the appropriate visitInternal() method via reflection.
  • Sets up defaulting to trying interface implementations for a given node class (if the specific node class does not have visitInternal() defined).

To create a visitor:

  1. Subclass this class.
  2. Implement visitInternal() methods for some specific ExprNode classes and perhaps for some interfaces as well.

    This is what happens when visit() is called on a node:

    • if the specific visitInternal() for that node class is implemented, then it is called,
    • else if one of the node class's interfaces has an implemented visitInternal(), then that method is called (with ties broken by approximate specificity of the interface)
    • else an UnsupportedOperationException is thrown.
  3. Implement a constructor (taking appropriate parameters for your visitor call), and perhaps implement a getResult() method or something similar for retrieving the result of the call.
  4. Implement reset().
